So… what you’re saying is that I’m a monstera leaf? (swipe left to see the unfolding of a new leaf from my beautiful monster plan). 

See below👇 

Ok, let’s get real. When starting therapy for the first time we may have questions such as: “how long will this take?” or “how come I’m not seeing any changes after one session? You might experience worries like, “what if this is a waste of time?” or “what if I’m in therapy for way longer than I hoped for?”

The questions you have and the worries you are experience make sense, especially if we hold the expectation that we should see changes asap. In therapy, the focus is on progress and not perfection. Progress can look so different for many people, whether that progress is developing deeper insight, self-awareness, and introspection. It could look like a softening of mental health symptoms, making the decision to book your first therapy session, and more importantly, showing up to that first session despite experience fear, anxiety; and worry.

Here is a question on this sunny Monday in Toronto, Canada: What does progress mean to you?

Reminder: Instagram is not therapy and does not replace progressional support. Content on this page is for educational and entertainment purposes only. 

#therapy #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #mentalillness #firstsession #depression #anxiety #mentalhealthadvocate #mentalhealthsupport #mentalhealthrecovery

~WORRYING~ chronic worrying can feel extremely exhausting and debilitating. Chronic worrying can lead to other challenges such as depression, hopelessness, tension, and stress. You might find that you have difficulty relaxing and finding relief day-to-day. Here’s a reminder: it IS possible to minimize worrying and live a more meaningful life.

I am accepting clients who reside in Ontario, Canada. Book a free consult by emailing me at mikayla@theupsidepractice.ca and let’s talk about your anxiety and worry.

#therapyiscool #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #therapy #anxiety #worry #mentalhealthrecovery

Let’s talk SOCIAL ANXIETY! People living with social anxiety often assume that others are holding critical thoughts about them. People may experience fear of judgement, fear of being criticized, or even fear that they will look weird. People can often make assumptions about what the other person is thinking when in reality what they are thinking is COMPLETELY different from the assumption. Remember assumptions are NOT facts ❤️

#socialanxiety #therapyiscool #therapyworks #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #anxiety

We’re delighted to welcome Mikayla Rukavina aka @whatsthetea.therapy to @healing_collective! Mikayla is a Social Worker/Psychotherapist who works with adults, specializing in supporting clients with ADHD. 

On her practice, Mikayla says,
 

“My areas of specialization include supporting young adults living with ADHD, general anxiety, social anxiety, and depression.

My goal as a therapist is for us to work together to understand the connection between your emotions, thoughts, behaviours, and physical sensations. Together, we can begin to develop awareness and deeper insight into when you started feeling this way, make connections between past experiences and present challenges, and learn skills to help you live a more fulfilling life.Most of my learning and inspiration comes from my clients and this guides my practice, challenges me to grow, and helps me to modify my approach to match what you need for therapy to feel effective.”

Mikayla is open to new clients and has sliding scale spots available. To book a complimentary consultation with her, you can contact us directly at info@healingcollective.ca or contact her directly via the link in our profile.

#therapy #mentalhealth #adhd #adhdawareness #adhdlife #adhdsupport #psychotherapy #wellness #mindfulness

But like that was funny, right?

OK SO - dark humour in therapy can provide you with some relief and provide some means of connection through a difficult time. Dark humour can also be a coping mechanism to avoid having to connect with difficult emotions and/or pain. Through therapy, you can learn to connect with these emotions despite the experience feeling uncomfortable. ❤️

#mentalhealth #mentalhealthmatters #pedropascal #therapyworks #anxiety #depression #trauma

Taking that first step and reaching out for mental health support is hard and I want to guide you on that process. I am currently accepting both in-person and virtual therapy clients who live in Ontario, Canada. You can contact me by emailing mikayla@theupsidepractice.ca. You can also check out my website to learn more about me: www.theupsidepractice.ca. #therapyiscool #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealthrecovery

Through lived and painful experiences, I knew I wanted to help others who have gone through their own adversity. I guess you could say that through pain I found passion - what a beautiful dialectic that is! I am so excited to be starting a private practice to help people feel seen, validated, and safe. You are NOT alone. 

#mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealth #therapy

I want you to remember that the therapy process is not linear. There are going to be days where you are feeling okay and can take on anything life throws at you. There are also going to be days where finding strength to get through the day feels so hard. Going to therapy is like riding a roller coaster (with a few upside down loops along the way). Just because it feels like you have taken a few steps back, progress is still being made. 

#mentalhealth #therapy #mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealthawareness

We gotta love those waves emotions! Okay, but seriously, it can feel exhausting 🥵 

Oh gosh, wouldn’t it be nice if we could just say, “surfs up!” and we immediately feel relief and grounded? 

Emotions sometimes do feel like a wave - they can change in intensity and frequency (and damn, this feels uncomfortable!). Regulation is key in helping to manage the range of emotions that rise up (like a big wave 🌊) through self-soothing. Also, with the help of a professional, you can learn keep a working distance from the emotions coming up and to help you stay within your Window of Tolerance (the place where intense emotions can be processed in a healthy way).

I’m curious to learn how you self-soothe when we’re are faced with surfing those big waves of emotions?

[Instagram is not therapy and does not replace professional support. This content is for entertainment and educational purposes only].

#mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealth #mentalhealthrecovery

I think boundaries are my favourite thing (aside from plants, coffee, and my dog). Learning to set boundaries can be difficult, especially if, for so long, other people have continuously broke them and made you feel uncomfortable. 

Learning to set boundaries with people who are causing you to experience distress, discomfort, and make you feel worse is so damn hard AND it’s time to start learning how put those boundaries in place to feel more grounded. Other people’s negative reactions to setting boundaries is not your shit to carry and is even more evidence to show that this person/people needed the boundary. 

[instagram is not therapy and does not replace professional support. This content is for education and entertainment purposes only]

Hiyah! My name is Mikayla and I wanted to welcome anyone new who has stumbled upon my page! ☺️

I am passionate about normalizing vulnerability and going to therapy. 

My approach as a therapist is emotion-focused and I do this work to help people live a more grounded, peaceful, and meaningful life! ✨ 

I love making reels and posting content for educational purposes and to make people laugh! 🤗

I have recently founded a practice called The Upside: www.theupsidepractice.ca

In naming this practice, I was inspired by my own lived experience with depression, anxiety, and ADHD. 

Right now it might feel like there is no up in sight AND I want to help you see that there can be.

I am so happy that you’re here and following along! 

Sometimes you might see my dog Sarah make appearances in my stories or reels. She is a gem and a rescue from Antigua! 🌍 

If you’re interested in booking a free 15 minute consult and getting started with therapy, you can send me an email: mikayla.theupside@gmail.com

#mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #adhd #anxiety #depression
